  "description": "Capgo before 12.128.2 contains an authorization bypass vulnerability where write-scoped API keys can directly mutate protected channel configuration fields through PostgREST by exploiting a null authentication check in the immutability trigger. Attackers with write API keys can modify sensitive channel attributes such as public, allow_emulator, and security-related flags outside intended application routes.",
